jobs.prompt:
Write two migrations under Code&DBs/Databases/migrations/workflow/ and register them in the authority.

1. Code&DBs/Databases/migrations/workflow/202_tenant_and_pool_sentinels.sql

Add ALTER TABLE ... ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS clauses so this migration is idempotent and safe to re-run.

- ALTER TABLE workflow_runs          ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS tenant_id        TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'praxis';
- ALTER TABLE workflow_runs          ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS resource_pool_id TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'default';
- ALTER TABLE workflow_chains        ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS tenant_id        TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'praxis';
- ALTER TABLE workflow_triggers      ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS tenant_id        TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'praxis';
- ALTER TABLE capability_grants      ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS tenant_id        TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'praxis';
- ALTER TABLE approval_requests      ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS tenant_id        TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'praxis';
- ALTER TABLE mobile_sessions        ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS tenant_id        TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'praxis';

If any of capability_grants / approval_requests / mobile_sessions do not yet exist (Phase 1 migrations 185–188 create them), wrap those ALTERs in a DO block that checks pg_class.relname IS NOT NULL first — the migration must still succeed if Phase 1 has not been applied yet. A warning NOTICE is fine.

Add COMMENT ON COLUMN for each tenant_id explaining 'SaaS readiness sentinel; always 'praxis' in single-tenant operation.' Add COMMENT ON COLUMN for workflow_runs.resource_pool_id explaining 'SaaS readiness sentinel; always 'default' until pool partitioning ships.'

Add partial indexes for future multi-tenant queries:
  CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS workflow_runs_tenant_pool_idx ON workflow_runs (tenant_id, resource_pool_id) WHERE tenant_id <> 'praxis' OR resource_pool_id <> 'default';

(The WHERE clause keeps the index empty in single-tenant mode so it costs nothing.)

2. Code&DBs/Databases/migrations/workflow/203_launch_admission_decisions.sql

CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS launch_admission_decisions (
  decision_id         TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  decided_at          TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),
  spec_path           TEXT NOT NULL,
  tenant_id           TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'praxis',
  resource_pool_id    TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'default',
  decision            TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (decision IN ('admitted','deferred','rejected')),
  reason              TEXT NOT NULL,
  signals             JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}'::jsonb,
  workflow_class_id   TEXT NULL,
  workflow_run_id     TEXT NULL,
  requested_by_kind   TEXT NULL,
  requested_by_ref    TEXT NULL
);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS launch_admission_decisions_decided_at_idx ON launch_admission_decisions (decided_at DESC);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS launch_admission_decisions_tenant_decided_idx ON launch_admission_decisions (tenant_id, decided_at DESC);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS launch_admission_decisions_run_idx ON launch_admission_decisions (workflow_run_id) WHERE workflow_run_id IS NOT NULL;
COMMENT ON TABLE launch_admission_decisions IS 'Ledger of every capacity-gate decision. Reactive today; predictive-scheduler training data tomorrow. Every admission/deferral/rejection from runtime/capacity/admission.py lands here.';

3. Register both migrations in Code&DBs/Workflow/system_authority/workflow_migration_authority.json (canonical_manifest, policy_buckets.canonical, expected_objects). Regenerate Code&DBs/Workflow/storage/_generated_workflow_migration_authority.py via python3 Code&DBs/Workflow/system_authority/generate_workflow_migration_authority.py.

expected_objects entries:
  "202_tenant_and_pool_sentinels.sql": [
    {"object_type": "column", "object_name": "workflow_runs.tenant_id"},
    {"object_type": "column", "object_name": "workflow_runs.resource_pool_id"},
    {"object_type": "column", "object_name": "workflow_chains.tenant_id"},
    {"object_type": "column", "object_name": "workflow_triggers.tenant_id"}
  ],
  "203_launch_admission_decisions.sql": [
    {"object_type": "table", "object_name": "launch_admission_decisions"}
  ]

Apply both migrations to the dev DB and confirm every ADD COLUMN and CREATE TABLE landed.
